organization.description: The State of Alaska contributes several collections of digital geospatial data and services for government and public use. The Dept of Geological and Geophysical Surveys and the Dept of Natural Resources publish data to data.gov. The University of Alaska also operates the AlaskaMapped and GINA repositories of data.

name: geochemical-trace-element-and-rare-earth-element-data-from-stream-sediment-and-pan-concentrate-
notes: Mineral-resources personnel from the Alaska Division of Geological & Geophysical Surveys conducted reconnaissance stream-sediment and pan-concentrate sampling in the Melozitna Mining District, Tanana and Melozitna quadrangles, from July 25 to August 13, 2011. This helicopter-supported sampling project was part of a statewide assessment of Alaska's potential for rare-earth element (REE) mineralization, and was funded by the Rare Earth Elements and Strategic Minerals Assessment capital improvement project. During this field project, 32 stream sediment and 28 heavy-mineral pan concentrate samples were collected for geochemical analysis (geochemical trace elements and rare earth elements). An additional historic U.S. Bureau of Mines sample from the area was also analyzed as part of this report. Highlights of the DGGS sampling project include documenting new gold-bearing drainages and identifying several samples with high REE values.
